entry.def: If something is replaceable, you can throw it away when it is finished and put a new one in its place.
If you say that someone is replaceable, you mean that they are not so important that someone else could not take their place.

example.ex: He would see I was not so easily replaceable.
example.tran: 他会看到我不是那么容易被替代的。
